// Figure D.1: CI/CD Pipeline Stages Overview
// Complete pipeline from trigger to notification

// ==================== TRIGGER ====================
Trigger [icon: git-pull-request, color: gray] {
  Push [icon: git-commit]
  Pull Request [icon: git-merge]
}

// ==================== BUILD STAGE ====================
Build [icon: package, color: blue] {
  .NET Build [icon: dotnet]
  Node Build [icon: nodejs]
}

// ==================== TEST STAGE ====================
Test [icon: check-circle, color: green] {
  Unit Tests [icon: test-tube]
  Lint [icon: search]
}

// ==================== SCAN STAGE ====================
Scan [icon: shield, color: yellow] {
  Trivy [icon: lock]
  CodeQL [icon: code]
}

// ==================== PUSH STAGE ====================
Push [icon: upload-cloud, color: purple] {
  ECR Push [icon: aws-ecr]
  Image Tag [icon: tag]
}

// ==================== DEPLOY STAGE ====================
Deploy [icon: rocket, color: orange] {
  Helm Install [icon: kubernetes]
  EKS Cluster [icon: aws-eks]
}

// ==================== VERIFY STAGE ====================
Verify [icon: eye, color: cyan] {
  Smoke Test [icon: activity]
  Health Check [icon: heart]
}

// ==================== NOTIFY STAGE ====================
Notify [icon: bell, color: pink] {
  Slack [icon: slack]
  Status [icon: check-square]
}

// ==================== PIPELINE FLOW ====================
Trigger > Build : on event
Build > Test : compile success
Test > Scan : tests pass
Scan > Push : no vulnerabilities
Push > Deploy : images pushed
Deploy > Verify : helm upgrade
Verify > Notify : deployment complete

// ==================== NOTES ====================
// This diagram represents the end-to-end CI/CD pipeline
// from code push to production deployment notification
